            <p>A dislocated shoulder is an injury in which your upper arm bone pops out of the cup-shaped socket that’s part of your shoulder blade. The muscles in your shoulder may spasm from the disruption, often increasing the intensity of your pain. However, once you’ve had a dislocated shoulder, your joint may become unstable and be prone to repeat dislocations.</p>
